%H A382845 <a href="/index/Rec#order_04">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (3,0,-3,1).
%F A382845 a(n) = A382843(n,1) + A382843(n,2).
%F A382845 a(n) = 2*Fibonacci(n)^2 - 1.
%F A382845 G.f.: -(1 - 4*x + 2*x^2 - x^3)/((1 - x)*(1 + x)*(1 - 3*x + x^2)). - _Andrew Howroyd_, Nov 12 2025
%e A382845 For n=4, the short leg is A382843(2,1) = 3 and the long leg is A382843(2,2) = 4  so the sum of the legs is then a(4) = 3 + 4 = 7.
%t A382845 a=Table[Fibonacci[n],{n,0,30}];Apply[Join,Map[{2#^2-1}&,a]]
%o A382845 (PARI) a(n) = 2*fibonacci(n)^2 - 1
